metadata.name: fx(splash) #63
metadata.description:
To celebrate fx(hash) turning 1 year old I've created this token as a part of the #fxhashturnsone event! It's a playful and colorful token symbolizing the experiences I've had with this platform.


The piece uses shaders to generate it's visuals which means that outputs will vary from device to device, and the preview might not look the exact same as your live view.

For that same reason I do not recommend running this piece on a mobile device as the shaders can be quite heavy and blurry on lower-tier hardware. My recommended way of viewing this token is on a pc.


--

To open the export menu double click the screen. Here you can export in a multitude of resolutions.

--


50% of primary proceeds will be donated to the processing foundation, learn more about them here:
https://processingfoundation.org

Made with opengl shaders and p5js by WootScoot, 2022.

metadata.name: Brush Strokes #69
metadata.description:
A piece trying to capture the raw and beatifull texture of brush strokes with thick paint. Has a total of four features:

- Swats: if yes, the piece will pick one color per brush stroke. If no, the piece will pick multiple colors per brush stroke. (the preview has swats)
- Color scheme: a total of 5 color schemes are available.
- Noise: applies to the hillyness of the terrain, if noise is high the artwork will seem more mountanous.
- Highlights: applies to the lighter / darker places of the artwork. If highlights is high these parts will be brighter / more accentuated.

As of rarity: 
Swats is 50/50, colors are all equal rarity, noise medium is 50% and low/high 25%, same applies to highlights.

metadata.name: Ontologies #100
metadata.description:
A system designed to make art out of its own code. 

What is the 'artful' component of generative art - is it the algorithm's form or the aesthetics of individual outputs? Ontologies brings the code out of the shadows into the foreground, nudging the viewer to consider this system's recursive existence. 

Is there something vaguely mortal, or at least vulnerable, about a system 'aware' of its own inner workings (like a person contemplating their DNA code)? Our use of computers to express incomputable human inspiration and creativity suggests that we already see them as more than just tools or calculating machines. So who is the artist, and what is the art?

Made with p5.js

metadata.name: Pixel Tunnel III #149
metadata.description:
This is based on a technique I've used to create textured abstract art by starting with a base design and applying millions of small mutations.

This design introduces generators and voids.

Generator: A block of color that continually reappears in the same location as the design generates.

Void: A black hole that appears near the end of the generation to break up the design and give visual relief.

- Higher themes are more rare (60 max)
- More colors are more rare (3 min, 6 max)
- Higher generator counts are more rare (5 min)
- There are 5 possible void patterns varying in rarity

metadata.name: System α #152
metadata.description:
"To capture the fleeting time in the generating process."

In this work,I d'like focus on the generating of generative art system itself rather than imitate some scene or style.
And with the flow of time, try to figure out where it can take me toward.

This work would be a series of my alternative view on generative art.
"α" means the first step of this series.

metadata.name: barcode(fxhash) #222
metadata.description:
[UPDATED: There was a bug in the first edition of this token that has been solved in this. All minters of the previous edition, has a reserve of 2]

barcode(fxhash) converts the ascii characters from the transaction hash of the token (fxhash variable) into barcodes for each of 51 characters. It uses Code 39 (https://github.com/graphicore/librebarcode), so it is not case sensitive. Each iteration has from 1 to 8 columns, and from 1 to 8 rows, and the frist N characters of the fxhash are displayed in one of first N positions (first 2 characters are discarted). If the number of characters is greater than 49 (length of fxhash discarting 'oo'), the boxes will continue to be filled, returning from the third character of fxhash.

Features generated by fxrand() random function:

-num_chars: number of characters displayed. from 1 to 64. They are the first N characters of fxhash.
-has_fxhash: this boolean value indicates whether fxhash contains the letters needed to form the word 'fxhash'.
-show_fxhash: this boolean value indicates whether fxhash contains the letters needed to form the word 'fxhash' and these are all displayed.
-columns: number of columns (1-8).
-rows: number of rows (1-8).
-color_mode: color mode white (light) or black (dark).
-separacio: factor of separation between barcodes (1.1, 1.5 or 2)
-scale_type: scale type (none, all, random, only rows, only columns, etc..)
-rotate_type: rotation type (none, all, random, only rows, only columns, etc..)
-transparent: this boolean value indicates whether the barcodes has a transparent background.
-squares: this boolean value indicates whether the barcodes width=height.
-main_shadow: blur value for main shadow.
-exterior_shadow: exterior shadow type rotation type (none, all, random, only rows, only columns, etc..)
-interior_shadow: exterior shadow type rotation type (none, all, random, only rows, only columns, etc..)


(There are more values generated by fxrand() not shown as Feature)

click to show all fxhash barcodes, wich are displayed.

metadata.name: Broken LCD Screen #137
metadata.description:
Millions of pixels gentle oscillating from side to side depicting a 4k broken LCD screen.
Capture taken at 12 seconds.
As ever there are lots of possible combinations of colors, pixelation and oscillated zoom levels.
This work also features a 10% of minting a rare dual-color token, which are usually made from a distinct Red, Blue or Green pixel set
Best seen in full screen mode.

Created by HicPunks using hydra on FX Hash 27th May 2022
@HicPunks

metadata.name: GEN XYZ Das Occult #9115
metadata.description:
A 10k Generative Profile Pic collection
GEN XYZ Das Occult - by culla - @tamccullough

move over cryptopunks
there is a new group on the scene

100% code - not an image composition

A bunch of common palettes
A selection of rare palettes
And a smaller set of ultra rare palettes
However, rarity will be based on what combinations the code produces

The majority of tokens will not have a special trait
However your token might have one or even multiple special traits
But, be aware that only the last special trait added will be listed in the features

Even then, look closely, because not all aspects of the canvas are included in the features. Collectors should still look closely and choose what they like when buying on secondary.

Which team are you on? X or O?

follow culla on twitter for updates. Or maybe __acolyte__

If the non reserved tokens mint out quickly, Access List mints will have 24 hours to mint reserves assigned to those wallets

2x for each Basqunk held
